  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This synthetic package embeds a future-dated evidence node (W-CON-03) in which one ValidationResult carries an evidenceTimestamp strictly after the UnitOfAssurance signatureTimestamp; the narrative does not address the discrepancy.",
